`crates/ctx-brief` is a binary crate producing executor-facing brief
markdown files from a `docs/STATUS.md` item or free-text ask, by driving
Claude twice against a target repo so that repo's own context hooks fire.
Depending on this crate gets you a CLI (`ctx-brief`) and its output
contract (a markdown file under `.context/.reports/briefs/`), not a
library API.

`src/` holds the full pipeline — CLI parsing, config construction,
orchestration, and the `Fs`/`Claude` trait seams — behind a single
`BriefError` type, with `contract.rs` guarding CLI/output docs against
drift. `tests/` exercises `runner::run` end-to-end against fakes
(`FakeFs`, `FakeClaude`) standing in for those seams, pinning
headless/interactive behavior and the literal output path
`.context/.reports/briefs/item.md`.

The two subtrees are coupled only through that seam boundary: any change
to `runner::Config`'s shape, the `Fs`/`Claude` trait signatures, or the
output-path derivation in `cli.rs::slug()`/`to_config()` must be
reflected in `tests/common`'s fakes and call-count assumptions, or the
test suite silently stops testing what runner actually does. `cwd` for
both Claude invocations must stay pinned to the target repo — this
invariant is asserted in three places in `src/` and exercised implicitly
by the integration tests.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.